726634f-a.text:
Flushing Meadow Park (Queens): At the north end of the park, near the mouth of the Flushing River. View 2 shows W.P.A. workmen cutting pampas grass at 114th Street and 38th Avenue, and view 3 the north end of the park being improved for the 193940 World's Fair.
P. L. Sperr  View 1: September 29, 1935
NO REPRODUCTIONS  View 2: October 4, 1935
View 3: June 16, 1937
